---
source: crates/jig-cli/src/context.rs
expression: "render_human(&mock_server(), &v)"
---
Context — what claude-sonnet (anthropic dialect) receives from jig-mock-server v0.1.0  [nothing is sent to any API]

  system prompt                                         42 tok
    You are connected to a set of tools. Read the user's task and, if one of the available tools is appropriate, call exactly one tool to accomplish it. If no tool fits, answer in plain text.

  server instructions                                    8 tok
    (offered by the server; not sent by `jig bench` — see footer)
    A toy MCP server for exercising Jig.

  tools (3)                                            175 tok
  ├─ make_reservation                                   99 tok
  │    "Book a table. Demonstrates a nested object argument and an enum."
  │    date: string (required) — "ISO-8601 date."
  │    party: object (required)
  │      seating: string — one of [indoor, outdoor, bar]
  │      size: integer (required)
  ├─ echo                                               42 tok
  │    "Echo the provided text straight back."
  │    text: string (required) — "Text to echo."
  └─ always_fails                                       34 tok
       "A tool that always reports an error, for testing error paths."
       (no parameters)

  TOTAL context before the user's first word           217 tok  (claude-sonnet, approx)

This is the anthropic API rendering — what `jig bench` sends. Chat clients (Claude Desktop,
Cursor, …) may render tool context differently; per-client renderings are a future
milestone.
No API key is needed or used: context computes this locally and sends nothing to any
provider.
Server instructions are shown for reference but are not in the request body: `jig
bench` sends only the system prompt + tools.
~approx — counted with the o200k_base tokenizer as a proxy (Claude's tokenizer is not publicly available); use --exact-anthropic for the exact total
